node.text:
This week's One Good Thing is a surprising laundry tip that comes from one of Maxwell's friends in the theater business — since they have so many opportunities to put on the same costumes, but need to remove those annoying odors that get caught over time. Vodka, it turns out, is a perfect odor remover as it is odorless and colorless itself! 

Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.title: Why You Should Keep Vodka With Your Clothes

You’d think that putting soap in the dishwasher and running it with a load would clean the inside, but that’s not the case. For today’s One Good Thing, Maxwell is showing you the quickest, easiest way to get your dishwasher ✨sparkling✨, along with two other fun facts you probably didn’t know about your machine. 

Read more at the link in bio. #OneGoodThingAtHome

node.title: 3 Things You Probably Didn't Know About Your Dishwasher

node.text: Creating a cozy bedroom where we can rest, relax, and recharge is more important than ever, and @ayeshacurry’s Small/Cool bedroom achieves  just that. “The goal for creating this bedroom retreat was to showcase how neutral, calming tones can still translate into interesting design,” she says. “We mainly focused on infusing texture rather than bold color, creating contrast through natural elements like wood and metal instead.” Explore and shop Ayesha’s space at the link in bio. #SmallCool

node.title: Teeny Tour: Serenity Now with @ayeshacurry of @sweetjuly & @parisaoconnell
